The only option had in life was to become successful because nobody around me was.'.

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia When first started out in corporate @ Merrill Lynch, realized how EVERYONE was broke. Most of my peers would drive their BMW to work in Gucci Loafers and still be paycheck-to-paycheck paycheck-to While they're making $100k+ That's when to invest. realized that I needed'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I bought three properties in 2011, and then the other five properties were purchased over the next nine years In total, my portfolio was worth ~$6.7M when I retired and it was composed of over 50 units.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I didn't invest crazy amounts into any of these either. I primarily used the BRRRR strategy and kept buying undervalued multifamily properties in Miami for dirt cheap. The cash flow from these properties alone allowed me to retire.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I knew could live comfortably off of $20,000/m. As of 2019, my properties were cash flowing about the same (net). That's when I knew I could retire.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I didn't nvest because it was the "cool thing to do" It took a lot of sacrifices, long weekends, and long nights to get to this point. But it's all all worth it because now I can do whatever want with my time.'.
